By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday paid a surprise visit to the Nigeria Correctional Centre, Kuje in the Federal Capital Territory. His visit followed the Boko Haram attack on the prison facility by the dreaded Boko Haram insurgents where several terrorists and other inmates were freed.Meanwhile, the Permanent Secretary of the Ministry of Interior, Mister Shuaibu Belgore has confirmed that about 600 inmates escaped from the Kuje Correctional Centre following last night’s attack by suspected terrorists. During a visit to the facility, he explains that over 300 of the inmates have been retrieved and more are on the way. Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The suspended deputy commissioner of police, Abba Kyari, has been moved out of Kuje Prison after the terror attach on the facility. Several Inmates have escaped from Kuje Prisons following a Terror attack on the Facility on Wednesday night. The terrorists launched the attack around 10:30… In "Top Stories" By GAMI TADANYIGBE KUJE- The Minister of Defence, Bashir Magashi says 64 Boko Haram suspects escaped from the Kuje custodial after the attack on the facility on Tuesday night.Addressing newsmen after taking an assessment tour of the facility, the Minister said the attack started around 10:30pm with heavy gunfire and explosions.He… In "Metro" By IBIRONKE ARIYO ABUJA- The Nigerian Correctional Service (NCoS) has said that four inmates of the Kuje Custodial Centre died and 879 escaped during the attack by the unknown Gunmen.The Service Public Relations Officer (SPRO), Mr Abubakar Umar, confirmed this in a statement on Wednesday in Abuja.Umar said that the… In "News"